            "text": "Capacity Test Automation and Reporting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A capacity test answers a different question than a load test: not \"does the system meet its SLA at expected load?\" but \"at what load does the system stop meeting its SLA, and what breaks first?\" Knowing the saturation point lets you set safe traffic limits, plan scaling triggers, and negotiate realistic capacity budgets with Anthropic."
          }
        ]
